text: Alice Grófová (married name Chladeková), is a female former Czechoslovak international table tennis player. She won a silver medal in the women's singles and a bronze medal in the mixed doubles with Josef Dvořáček at the 1973 World Table Tennis Championships. She also won an English Open title. ==See also== * List of table tennis players * List of World Table Tennis Championships medalists ==References== Category:Slovak female table tennis players Category:World Table Tennis Championships medalists
title: Alice Grófová
